Echo sample supervisor reads SIC input from HLOS and and writes the same
data back.

In addition, echo supervisor can be used to test user mode threads
(set CONFIG_TEST_USER_THREADS=y in prj.conf) and user mode containers
(set CONFIG_TEST_USER_CONTAINERS=y in prj.conf).

The main supervisor mode thread reads SIC flow 0, possible user mode thread
reads SIC flow 1, possible user mode container thread reads SIC flow 2.

To send data to supervisor mode thread:
$ cmtest data -f0 "hello"

To send data to user mode thread:
$ cmtest data -f1 "hello"

To send data to user container thread, first load the echo container
to the main thread using flow 0, then send data to flow 2:
$ cmtest data -f0 containers/echo/echo.img
$ cmtest data -f2 "hello"

Supervisor mode logs for echo supervisor with all config options set:
$ cmtest data -f0 containers/echo/echo.img
$ cmtest data -f0 "hello"
$ cmtest data -f1 "hello"
$ cmtest data -f2 "hello"
$ cmtest log
